    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-11-03T06:12:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-11-03T06:12:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>199. Telegram From the Embassy in Italy to the Department of State<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d199fn1">Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential
                        Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 695, Country
                        Files—Europe, Italy, Vol. II. Confidential; Priority; <gloss
                            target="#t_Exdis_1">Exdis</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Rome</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-11-03T11:12:00+00:00">November 3, 1970,
                        1112Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6311. Subject: <gloss target="#t_Chirec_1">Chirec</gloss>.</p>
                <p>1. Foreign Ministry Secretary General <persName corresp="#p_GR_1">Gaja</persName>
                    has requested Chargé to call on him at 7:00 p.m. this evening, Rome time. GRC
                    Ambassador has been asked by <persName corresp="#p_GR_1">Gaja</persName> come at
                    6:00 p.m. We understand from separate source that purpose is to inform GRC
                    Ambassador and US of <gloss target="#t_GOI_1">GOI</gloss>’s intention to
                    announce recognition <gloss target="#t_PRC_1">PRC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>2. Final Paris meeting now scheduled for tomorrow, November 4, to confirm and
                    sign joint communiqué. If no hitches develop, recognition announcement will take
                    place November 6.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_SW_2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SW_2">Stabler</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
